comments.body:
I think we should update the comments here for `Provide`. Maybe something like:
```
// Provide returns docker configuration.
// Implementations can be blocking - e.g. metadata server unavailable.
// The image is passed into Provide in the event that the implementation depends on any information
// in the image URL (e.g. the region where the repo is). The image can be ignored otherwise.
```

In general I agree but think that the parenthetical is a little to leading to the AWS use-case. Would instead propose:

```
// Provide returns docker configuration.
// Implementations can be blocking - e.g. metadata server unavailable.
// The image is passed into Provide as context in the event that the implementation depends 
// on information in the image name to return credentials, implementations are safe to ignore this.
```

